
# Debugging guide

## Arduino UNO

### Requirements

Visual Studio Code \
PlatformIO extension on Visual Studio Code \
libncurses5 (A PlatformIO dependency)

```bash
sudo apt-get install libncurses5
```

### Setup

1. Go into the debug source directory.
```bash
cd ./debug/ArduinoDebugIO/src 
```

2. Create a symbolink link with the Arduino ".ino" file you wish to debug in the current debug source directory.

Example:
```bash
ln -s ../../../prototype/FFT_image_processing/arduino_image_processing/arduino_image_processing.ino
```

3. Add all source files dependencies in the current debug source directory.
Example:
```bash
ln -s ../../../src/FFT.c
```
```bash
ln -s ../../../prototype/utils/arduino_serial_port.cpp
```

4. From the current debug source directory, go to the debug header directory.
```bash
cd ./../include
```

5. Add all header files dependencies in the current debug header directory.
Example:
```bash
ln -s ../../../src/FFT.h
```
```bash
ln -s ../../../prototype/utils/arduino_serial_port.h
```

6. 


